@startuml validate-catalog-schema
' ============================================================
' Validate Catalog Schema - CI Gate Workflow
' Source: .github/workflows/validate-catalog-schema.yml
' A0/A3 exit gate for catalog/images.yaml and
' catalog/approved-lock.yaml; REQUIRED status check on main.
' ============================================================

!define ARROW_COLOR #2C3E50
!define GATE_COLOR  #D32F2F
!define PASS_COLOR  #2E7D32

skinparam activity {
  BackgroundColor        #F5F5F5
  BorderColor            #455A64
  FontName               Helvetica
  FontSize               11
  ArrowColor             #2C3E50
  ArrowFontSize          10
  StartColor             #263238
  EndColor               #263238
  DiamondBackgroundColor #FFF9C4
  DiamondBorderColor     #F57F17
  DiamondFontSize        10
}

skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #E3F2FD
  BorderColor     #1565C0
  FontSize        10
}

skinparam legend {
  BackgroundColor #FAFAFA
  BorderColor     #B0BEC5
  FontSize        10
}

title Validate Catalog Schema\n<size:10>//A0/A3 exit gate -- required status check on main//</size>

' ============================================================
' TRIGGERS
' ============================================================

|Triggers|
start

note right
  **Trigger matrix**
  //push// to main -- paths:
    catalog/images.yaml
    catalog/approved-lock.yaml
    scripts/validate_catalog_schema.py
    scripts/verify_approved_lock.py
    scripts/build_matrix.py
    tests/**
    .github/workflows/validate-catalog-schema.yml
  //merge_group//
  //workflow_dispatch//
end note

note right #FFCDD2
  **#CRITICAL -- required status check**
  The //pull_request// trigger carries **no** //paths://
  filter by design. A required status check must
  report a result on **every** PR to main. Adding
  a //paths:// filter causes non-matching PRs to be
  skipped -- GitHub never reports a result -- and
  the PR becomes stuck on:
  "Expected - Waiting for status to be reported."
  **Never re-add paths: here unless this check is**
  **removed from branch protection first.**
  //Source: validate-catalog-schema.yml:27-35//
end note

:Workflow triggered;

' ============================================================
' JOB: validate (ubuntu-latest, timeout 5 min)
' ============================================================

|validate job\n(ubuntu-latest, 5 min timeout)|

' --- Step 1 ---
#LightBlue:1. Harden Runner\n<size:9>step-security/harden-runner@9af89fc (v2.19.4)\negress-policy: audit</size>;
note right
  **Source:**
  .github/workflows/
    validate-catalog-schema.yml:55-58
end note

' --- Step 2 ---
#LightBlue:2. Checkout repository\n<size:9>actions/checkout@9c091bb (v7)\npersist-credentials: false</size>;
note right
  **Source:**
  validate-catalog-schema.yml:60-63
end note

' --- Step 3 ---
#LightBlue:3. Set up Python 3.12\n<size:9>actions/setup-python@ece7cb0 (v6.3.0)</size>;
note right
  **Source:**
  validate-catalog-schema.yml:65-68
end note

' --- Step 4 ---
#LightBlue:4. Install dependencies\n<size:9>pip install pyyaml pytest</size>;
note right
  **Source:**
  validate-catalog-schema.yml:70-71
end note

' --- Step 5: pip-audit ---
#FFF3E0:5. Audit dependencies\n<size:9>pip install pip-audit && pip-audit\nDependency CVE scan</size>;
note right
  **Source:**
  validate-catalog-schema.yml:73-76
  **Purpose:** detect known CVEs in
  pyyaml, pytest, pip-audit itself
end note

if (CVEs found?) then (yes -- fail)
  #FFCDD2:FAIL: dependency audit;\n-> merge blocked;
  stop
else (no -- pass)
endif

' --- Step 6: schema gate ---
#E8F5E9:**6. Validate catalog schema**\n<size:9>python3 scripts/validate_catalog_schema.py\n       catalog/images.yaml\nA0 gate: required fields, enums, GHCR ref\nuniqueness, upstream/platform shape</size>;
note right
  **Source gate:**
  validate-catalog-schema.yml:78-79
  scripts/validate_catalog_schema.py
  Input: catalog/images.yaml
  Checks: required fields, source_tier,
  criticality, disposition, GHCR ref
  uniqueness, platform_compatibility
end note

if (Schema errors?) then (yes -- fail)
  #FFCDD2:FAIL: catalog schema gate;\n-> merge blocked;
  stop
else (no -- pass)
endif

' --- Step 7: A3 provenance gate ---
#E8F5E9:**7. Verify approved-lock provenance**\n<size:9>python3 scripts/verify_approved_lock.py\n       catalog/approved-lock.yaml\n       catalog/images.yaml\nA3 gate: schema + source==target digest\n+ catalog cross-reference</size>;
note right
  **Source gate:**
  validate-catalog-schema.yml:81-84
  scripts/verify_approved_lock.py
  Inputs: approved-lock.yaml,
          images.yaml
  Checks:
    (a) schema: required fields, kind
    (b) source_digest == target_digest
    (c) digest format sha256:<64hex>
    (d) id present in catalog
    (e) ghcr_ref matches catalog
    (f) id uniqueness in lock
  Output: trusted approved-lock.yaml
end note

if (Provenance errors?) then (yes -- fail)
  #FFCDD2:FAIL: A3 provenance gate;\n-> merge blocked;
  stop
else (no -- pass)
endif

' --- Step 8: pytest ---
#E8F5E9:**8. Run tests**\n<size:9>python3 -m pytest tests/ -v --tb=short\nHappy-path + bypass-attempt cases</size>;
note right
  **Source:**
  validate-catalog-schema.yml:86-87
  Scope: tests/**
  Covers: valid catalog acceptance,
  tampered-digest bypass attempts,
  null-field bypass attempts,
  duplicate-id rejection
end note

if (Tests fail?) then (yes -- fail)
  #FFCDD2:FAIL: pytest suite;\n-> merge blocked;
  stop
else (no -- pass)
endif

' --- Step 9: dry-run matrix build ---
#E8F5E9:**9. Dry-run matrix build**\n<size:9>python3 scripts/build_matrix.py\n       catalog/images.yaml\nVerify matrix builder parses\nvalidated catalog without error</size>;
note right
  **Source:**
  validate-catalog-schema.yml:89-90
  scripts/build_matrix.py
  Input: catalog/images.yaml
  (catalog already validated above)
end note

if (Matrix build fails?) then (yes -- fail)
  #FFCDD2:FAIL: dry-run matrix build;\n-> merge blocked;
  stop
else (no -- pass)
endif

' ============================================================
' SUCCESS
' ============================================================

#C8E6C9:**All gates passed**\n<size:9>approved-lock.yaml is the trusted output\nRequired status check reports: SUCCESS\nPR merge to main is unblocked</size>;

stop

' ============================================================
' LEGEND
' ============================================================

legend bottom
  |= Color |= Meaning |
  |<#LightBlue>      | Environment / setup step |
  |<#FFF3E0>      | Security audit gate |
  |<#E8F5E9>      | Validation gate (blocks merge on failure) |
  |<#FFCDD2>      | Failure -- merge blocked |
  |<#C8E6C9>      | Success -- merge unblocked |

  **Required check:** "Validate catalog schema"
  **Branch protection:** targets main; gates ALL pull_request events
  **Job:** validate | ubuntu-latest | timeout 5 min | permissions: contents read
endlegend

@enduml
